criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria:

          -  Age above 18 and under 45 at the time of inclusion;

          -  Sign the informed consent form.

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  Be indigenous;

          -  Active TB or previous use of isoniazid;

          -  Score Alcohol Use Disorders Identification Test ≥15.

          -  Reactive serology for HIV, hepatitis B and C;

          -  Reactive result for quantiferon, considering as positive the result of Tube 1 and / or
             Tube22 above 0.2 IU / mL;

          -  Liver enzymes (Aspartate aminotransferase and Alanate aminotransferase) three times
             the upper limit;

          -  History or treatment for epilepsy;
